Because many people see him as an ordinary person wronged by the authorities and as a hero who stood up to power, they come to him to express their frustration that justice and righteousness havenâ€™t prevailed.

They are angry that only two police officers have been punished for reprimanding him. Many believe the police were acting on orders from higher up.

They also share their relief that Chinaâ€™s lockdowns appear to be nearing an end, their distrust of the official news and their lingering fear of the pandemic.

